## 9. TECH STACK CONSIDERATIONS

**Inherited from FluidCalendar**: Next.js 15, TypeScript, Prisma, Postgres, FullCalendar, NextAuth, Tailwind. We work with this stack, not against it.

**Additions over time**:
- OpenAI API integration for parsing, clarifying, Now Mode reasoning, sprint planning (server-side calls only, no exposed keys)
- Web Push library for PWA notifications
- Web Speech API for voice input (browser-native, no extra dep)
- Framer Motion (if not already present) for the motion specs above
- Lucide React for icons (likely already present)

**Future considerations** (not Phase 1):
- Capacitor wrapper for native iOS app (App Store, real push notifications, Siri Shortcuts)
- Tauri wrapper for native Mac desktop app
- Tailscale or Cloudflare Tunnel for secure VPS access without public exposure

**What we don't add unless proven necessary**:
- New JS frameworks (we live in Next.js)
- A separate companion app (architecture stays unified)
- Real-time collaboration features (this is a personal tool)

