## 12. THE TEST FOR EVERY CHANGE

Before merging, ask:

**Does it serve a brain under load?**

If yes → consider it.
If no → cut it, no matter how clever.

The user is one-handed on a phone, distracted, between meetings, mid-squirrel-moment. Every interaction should feel inevitable — and a little bit warm.